```php
<?php

namespace App\Http\Controllers;

use Illuminate\Http\Request;

class LaravelAppController extends Controller
{
    /**
     * Display the home page.
     *
     * @return \Illuminate\Http\Response
     */
    public function index()
    {
        return view('welcome');
    }

    /**
     * Handle the form submission.
     *
     * @param  \Illuminate\Http\Request  $request
     * @return \Illuminate\Http\Response
     */
    public function submitForm(Request $request)
    {
        // Handle form submission logic here

        return redirect()->back()->with('success', 'Form submitted successfully!');
    }
}
```

This is the code for the `app/Http/Controllers` file. It defines a `LaravelAppController` class with two methods: `index()` and `submitForm()`. The `index()` method returns the view for the home page, while the `submitForm()` method handles the form submission logic and redirects back to the previous page with a success message.